h225CallSignaling.description: The MIB Module supports the functions of a H.225 call signaling .

callSignalConfigTable.name: callSignalConfigTable
callSignalConfigTable.description: This table contains configuration information for instances of a call signaling protocol.

callSignalConfigEntry.name: callSignalConfigEntry
callSignalConfigEntry.description: It contains objects that describe the configuration.

callSignalConfigMaxConnections.name: callSignalConfigMaxConnections
callSignalConfigMaxConnections.description: The maximum number of connections the H.225 entity can possibly have.

callSignalConfigAvailableConnections.name: callSignalConfigAvailableConnections
callSignalConfigAvailableConnections.description: The number of available connections, out of callSignalConfigMaxConnections.

callSignalConfigT303.name: callSignalConfigT303
callSignalConfigT303.description: The amount of time the calling endpoint waits for an ALERTING, CALL PROCEEDING, CONNECT, RELEASE COMPLETE or other message the called endpoint after it has sent a SETUP message. The time value is in seconds.

callSignalConfigT301.name: callSignalConfigT301
callSignalConfigT301.description: The amount of time after which the calling endpoint should stop waiting for the called endpoint to respond. The time value is in seconds.

callSignalConfigEnableNotifications.name: callSignalConfigEnableNotifications
callSignalConfigEnableNotifications.description: Indicates whether notifications should be generated from this MIB. The default is disabled.

connectionsRole.description: This value reflects the role this entity plays in this connection being either a caller or a callee.

connectionsState.name: connectionsState
connectionsState.description: The state of the H.225 state machine as per Q.931. Outgoing calls: callInitiated - when the user requests call establishment from the network callDelivered - when the calling user has received an indication that remote user alerting has been initiated. Incoming calls: callPresent - when the user has received a call establishment but not yet responded. callReceived - when the user has indicated alerting but not yet answered. connectRequest - when the user has answered the call and is waiting to be awarded the call. Incoming/Outgoing: callProceeding - when the user has received/sent acknowledgement that the network has received all call information necessary to effect call establishment. active - when the user has received/sent an acknoledgement from/to the network that the user has been awarded the call. disconnectRequest - when the user has requested the network to clear the end-to-end connection. disconnectIndication - when the user has received an invitation to disconnect to disconnect because the network has disconnected the end-to-end connection. releaseRequest - when the user has requested the network to release and is waiting for a responce.

callReleaseComplete.description: This message will be sent in the case of on generation and reception of releaseComplete for the following reasons: 34 - noBandwidth; no circuit/channel available 47 - gatekeeperResources; resource unavailable 3 - unreachableDestination; no route to destination 16 - destinationReject; destination did not accept this call 88 - invalidRevision; incompatible destination 111- noPermission; Interworking unspecified 38 - unreachableGatekeeper; network out of order 42 - gatewayResources; switching equipment congestion 28 - badFormaTAddress; invalid number format 41 - adaptiveBusy; Temporary Failure 17 - inConference; user busy 31 - undefined.
